OL,3,C'Men in wigs and brown make-up taking
OL,4,Cstunt jobs from black women' ` study
OL,6,FDr Crossley also said that because the
OL,7,Fwork of stunt people is "invisible" to
OL,8,Fthe public, there is limited scrutiny
OL,9,Fof representation compared with acting
OL,10,Fand directing roles.
OL,12,FShe said this is worsened by the
OL,13,Findustry pushing the idea that actors
OL,14,Fperform their own stunts.
OL,16,FShe said the lack of female roles
OL,17,Fdates back to when Hollywood moved to
OL,18,Fthe studio system, and women were
OL,19,F"frozen out".
